solution.p:
This is a power equation. We divide both sides by 3 to isolate the variable, then raise both sides to the reciprocal of the exponent.
    (x^{1.05})^{1/1.05} \amp = 6^{1/1.05}
            x \amp = 5.51

This is a power equation. We divide both sides by 9 to isolate the variable, then raise both sides to the reciprocal of the exponent.
    (x^{3/5})^{5/3} \amp = 4^{5/3}
        x \amp = 10.08

The growth law for the population is P=P_0(1.038)^t. We set P=2P_0 and solve for t.
    2P_0 \amp = P_0(1.038)^t  \amp\amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by}~P_0.}
        2 \amp = (1.038)^t  \amp\amp \blert{\text{Take the log of both sides.}}
        \log 2 \amp = t \log 1.038  \amp\amp \blert{\text{Apply the third log property.}}
        t \amp = \dfrac{\log 2}{\log 1.038} = 18.59            
The doubling time is 18.59 years.

